snippet.textDisplay: Your art and many other peoples art inspires me to the artist I am. My art teacher which is more like a friend and my family all feel like I could be an artist. I’ve considered art school when I’m older but one of my fellow students keeps telling me I’m not going to be an artist. He tells me that just about everything I want to accomplish or have accomplished is a bad idea and I can’t do it. These are the people that I block out. The ones that push you down. My art project is going to be in an art museum and so is every one else’s. These are the people that I give constructive criticism to and they don’t like hearing it so they just flat out insult me to make me feel bad. Take this as a message to keep creating. Don’t let others push you down. Don’t be rude towards other artist, be nice and constructive. If you set a goal and your set in it you will make it.
